{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":400,"text":"Three years ago, I was standing about a hundred yards"},{"time":3489,"text":"from Chernobyl nuclear reactor number four."},{"time":7115,"text":"My Geiger counter dosimeter, which measures radiation,"},{"time":10262,"text":"was going berserk,"},{"time":11850,"text":"and the closer I got, the more frenetic it became,"},{"time":15297,"text":"and frantic. My God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18093,"text":"I was there covering the 25th anniversary"},{"time":20843,"text":"of the world's worst nuclear accident,"},{"time":23993,"text":"as you can see by the look on my face,"},{"time":25942,"text":"reluctantly so, but with good reason,"},{"time":28833,"text":"because the nuclear fire that burned for 11 days"},{"time":32296,"text":"back in 1986 released 400 times as much radiation"},{"time":36712,"text":"as the bomb dropped on Hiroshima,"},{"time":38928,"text":"and the sarcophagus, which is the covering"},{"time":41402,"text":"over reactor number four,"},{"time":42979,"text":"which was hastily built 27 years ago,"},{"time":45861,"text":"now sits cracked and rusted"},{"time":47779,"text":"and leaking radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49495,"text":"So I was filming."},{"time":51173,"text":"I just wanted to get the job done"},{"time":52479,"text":"and get out of there fast."},{"time":55066,"text":"But then, I looked into the distance,"},{"time":57350,"text":"and I saw some smoke coming from a farmhouse,"},{"time":60627,"text":"and I'm thinking, who could be living here?"},{"time":63170,"text":"I mean, after all, Chernobyl's soil, water and air,"},{"time":66762,"text":"are among the most highly contaminated on Earth,"},{"time":69472,"text":"and the reactor sits at the the center of"},{"time":71090,"text":"a tightly regulated exclusion zone, or dead zone,"},{"time":74736,"text":"and it's a nuclear police state, complete with border guards."},{"time":78081,"text":"You have to have dosimeter at all times, clicking away,"},{"time":80628,"text":"you have to have a government minder,"},{"time":82549,"text":"and there's draconian radiation rules"},{"time":85185,"text":"and constant contamination monitoring."},{"time":89890,"text":"The point being, no human being"},{"time":92042,"text":"should be living anywhere near the dead zone."},{"time":94928,"text":"But they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96521,"text":"It turns out an unlikely community"},{"time":99174,"text":"of some 200 people are living inside the zone."},{"time":102627,"text":"They're called self-settlers."},{"time":104485,"text":"And almost all of them are women,"},{"time":107125,"text":"the men having shorter lifespans"},{"time":108993,"text":"in part due to overuse of alcohol, cigarettes,"},{"time":111310,"text":"if not radiation."},{"time":113298,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of people were evacuated"},{"time":115536,"text":"at the time of the accident,"},{"time":117156,"text":"but not everybody accepted that fate."},{"time":119617,"text":"The women in the zone, now in their 70s and 80s,"},{"time":122410,"text":"are the last survivors of a group who defied authorities"},{"time":125405,"text":"and, it would seem, common sense,"},{"time":127355,"text":"and returned to their ancestral homes inside the zone."},{"time":131045,"text":"They did so illegally."},{"time":133529,"text":"As one woman put it to a soldier"},{"time":135446,"text":"who was trying to evacuate her for a second time,"},{"time":138260,"text":"\"Shoot me and dig the grave."},{"time":140083,"text":"Otherwise, I'm going home.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":142661,"text":"Now why would they return to such deadly soil?"},{"time":145196,"text":"I mean, were they unaware of the risks"},{"time":147104,"text":"or crazy enough to ignore them, or both?"},{"time":150115,"text":"The thing is, they see their lives"},{"time":151587,"text":"and the risks they run decidedly differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155119,"text":"Now around Chernobyl, there are scattered ghost villages,"},{"time":158372,"text":"eerily silent, strangely charming, bucolic,"},{"time":162703,"text":"totally contaminated."},{"time":164626,"text":"Many were bulldozed under at the time of the accident,"},{"time":167765,"text":"but a few are left like this,"},{"time":169798,"text":"kind of silent vestiges to the tragedy."},{"time":173351,"text":"Others have a few residents in them,"},{"time":175662,"text":"one or two \"babushkas,\" or \"babas,\""},{"time":178127,"text":"which are the Russian and Ukrainian words for grandmother."},{"time":181316,"text":"Another village might have six or seven residents."},{"time":184399,"text":"So this is the strange demographic of the zone --"},{"time":187129,"text":"isolated alone together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189998,"text":"And when I made my way to that piping chimney"},{"time":192201,"text":"I'd seen in the distance,"},{"time":193872,"text":"I saw Hanna Zavorotnya, and I met her."},{"time":197118,"text":"She's the self-declared mayor of Kapavati village,"},{"time":200184,"text":"population eight."},{"time":202146,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":204109,"text":"And she said to me, when I asked her the obvious,"},{"time":207342,"text":"\"Radiation doesn't scare me. Starvation does.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":211351,"text":"And you have to remember, these women have"},{"time":212984,"text":"survived the worst atrocities of the 20th century."},{"time":216852,"text":"Stalin's enforced famines of the 1930s, the Holodomor,"},{"time":220423,"text":"killed millions of Ukrainians,"},{"time":222254,"text":"and they faced the Nazis in the '40s,"},{"time":224277,"text":"who came through slashing, burning, raping,"},{"time":227253,"text":"and in fact many of these women"},{"time":228869,"text":"were shipped to Germany as forced labor."},{"time":231954,"text":"So when a couple decades into Soviet rule,"},{"time":234414,"text":"Chernobyl happened,"},{"time":235609,"text":"they were unwilling to flee in the face of an enemy"},{"time":238671,"text":"that was invisible."},{"time":240849,"text":"So they returned to their villages"},{"time":242838,"text":"and are told they're going to get sick and die soon,"},{"time":246058,"text":"but five happy years, their logic goes,"},{"time":248623,"text":"is better than 10 stuck in a high rise"},{"time":251178,"text":"on the outskirts of Kiev,"},{"time":253038,"text":"separated from the graves of their mothers"},{"time":255216,"text":"and fathers and babies,"},{"time":257536,"text":"the whisper of stork wings on a spring afternoon."},{"time":261492,"text":"For them, environmental contamination"},{"time":263890,"text":"may not be the worst sort of devastation."},{"time":266440,"text":"It turns out this holds true"},{"time":267760,"text":"for other species as well."},{"time":269851,"text":"Wild boar, lynx, moose, they've all returned"},{"time":272798,"text":"to the region in force,"},{"time":274548,"text":"the very real, very negative effects of radiation"},{"time":277803,"text":"being trumped by the upside of a mass exodus"},{"time":281361,"text":"of humans."},{"time":283112,"text":"The dead zone, it turns out, is full of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287805,"text":"And there is a kind of heroic resilience,"},{"time":290863,"text":"a kind of plain-spoken pragmatism to those"},{"time":293734,"text":"who start their day at 5 a.m."},{"time":296226,"text":"pulling water from a well"},{"time":298469,"text":"and end it at midnight"},{"time":300173,"text":"poised to beat a bucket with a stick"},{"time":302237,"text":"and scare off wild boar that might mess with their potatoes,"},{"time":305137,"text":"their only company a bit of homemade moonshine vodka."},{"time":310289,"text":"And there's a patina of simple defiance among them."},{"time":313699,"text":"\"They told us our legs would hurt, and they do. So what?\""},{"time":317537,"text":"I mean, what about their health?"},{"time":319239,"text":"The benefits of hardy, physical living,"},{"time":322061,"text":"but an environment made toxic"},{"time":323665,"text":"by a complicated, little-understood enemy, radiation."},{"time":327648,"text":"It's incredibly difficult to parse."},{"time":329783,"text":"Health studies from the region"},{"time":331600,"text":"are conflicting and fraught."},{"time":334340,"text":"The World Health Organization"},{"time":335733,"text":"puts the number of Chernobyl-related deaths"},{"time":338463,"text":"at 4,000, eventually."},{"time":340781,"text":"Greenpeace and other organizations"},{"time":343419,"text":"put that number in the tens of thousands."},{"time":346577,"text":"Now everybody agrees that thyroid cancers"},{"time":349569,"text":"are sky high, and that Chernobyl evacuees"},{"time":352186,"text":"suffer the trauma of relocated peoples everywhere:"},{"time":355253,"text":"higher levels of anxiety, depression, alcoholism,"},{"time":358531,"text":"unemployment and, importantly,"},{"time":360711,"text":"disrupted social networks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363954,"text":"Now, like many of you,"},{"time":366360,"text":"I have moved maybe 20, 25 times in my life."},{"time":370985,"text":"Home is a transient concept."},{"time":374407,"text":"I have a deeper connection to my laptop"},{"time":376584,"text":"than any bit of soil."},{"time":380926,"text":"So it's hard for us to understand, but home"},{"time":383165,"text":"is the entire cosmos of the rural babushka,"},{"time":386338,"text":"and connection to the land is palpable."},{"time":389794,"text":"And perhaps because these Ukrainian women"},{"time":391585,"text":"were schooled under the Soviets"},{"time":393588,"text":"and versed in the Russian poets,"},{"time":395830,"text":"aphorisms about these ideas"},{"time":397388,"text":"slip from their mouths all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399585,"text":"\"If you leave, you die.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":402592,"text":"\"Those who left are worse off now."},{"time":404559,"text":"They are dying of sadness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":406200,"text":"\"Motherland is motherland. I will never leave.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":410687,"text":"What sounds like faith, soft faith,"},{"time":413943,"text":"may actually be fact,"},{"time":417068,"text":"because the surprising truth --"},{"time":418690,"text":"I mean, there are no studies, but the truth seems to be"},{"time":421076,"text":"that these women who returned to their homes"},{"time":423648,"text":"and have lived on some of the most radioactive land"},{"time":425728,"text":"on Earth for the last 27 years,"},{"time":427934,"text":"have actually outlived their counterparts"},{"time":430289,"text":"who accepted relocation,"},{"time":432336,"text":"by some estimates up to 10 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436462,"text":"How could this be?"},{"time":438642,"text":"Here's a theory: Could it be"},{"time":440341,"text":"that those ties to ancestral soil,"},{"time":443406,"text":"the soft variables reflected in their aphorisms,"},{"time":445972,"text":"actually affect longevity?"},{"time":448836,"text":"The power of motherland"},{"time":450595,"text":"so fundamental to that part of the world"},{"time":453053,"text":"seems palliative."},{"time":454865,"text":"Home and community are forces"},{"time":457662,"text":"that rival even radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461722,"text":"Now radiation or not,"},{"time":464200,"text":"these women are at the end of their lives."},{"time":466804,"text":"In the next decade, the zone's human residents will be gone,"},{"time":470797,"text":"and it will revert to a wild, radioactive place,"},{"time":475024,"text":"full only of animals and occasionally"},{"time":478138,"text":"daring, flummoxed scientists."},{"time":481230,"text":"But the spirit and existence of the babushkas,"},{"time":484332,"text":"whose numbers have been halved"},{"time":486039,"text":"in the three years I've known them,"},{"time":488181,"text":"will leave us with powerful new templates"},{"time":490379,"text":"to think about and grapple with,"},{"time":492395,"text":"about the relative nature of risk,"},{"time":496058,"text":"about transformative connections to home,"},{"time":499905,"text":"and about the magnificent tonic"},{"time":503451,"text":"of personal agency and self-determination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507304,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509239,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}